Tibetan words should never end with a ཚེག (tsheg), which is an intersyllabic marker.  It would be like leaving an extra space on an English word, for no reason, except with more visual clutter.  They should either end in a ཤད (shad, i.e. །), or—preferably—with nothing at all, when used alone (this is also the standard on Wiktionary, for example).
